title: Judge temporarily halts Trump's limited gag order in election interference case
description: The federal judge overseeing former President Trump's election interference case has temporarily halted the limited gag order she placed on him on Monday.

title: Progressives call for ceasefire: 'Vengeance is not a foreign policy doctrine'
description: Progressive Reps. Cori Bush, Ayanna Pressley and Ilhan Omar call for a ceasefire in Gaza following the Hamas terrorist attack on Israel.

title: Perry Johnson suspends long shot presidential campaign
description: Perry Johnson suspends his long shot presidential campaign, but he hasn't said whether or not he'll drop his FEC complaint against the RNC.

title: Fisher-Price recalls about 21,000 Thomas & Friends truck toys
description: Fisher-Price and the CPSC have issued a recall of Thomas & Friends Wooden Railway Troublesome Truck & Crates and Troublesome Truck & Paint toys.

title: Spirit Airlines cancels dozens of flights to inspect some planes
description: Spirit Airlines is canceling about 100 flights because it's pulling some planes out of service for inspections

title: 60,000 gun safes recalled after shooting death
description: Thousands of gun safes have been recalled after one person allegedly died from a firearm obtained from one of the safes.

title: Toddler 'formulas' unnecessary and lack nutritional benefits, pediatrician group says
description: Toddler formula, also known as toddler milk, is marketed as the next step for babies one year or older.

title: Juveniles charged with dousing acid on playground slides that injured 4 children
description: A Massachusetts prosecutor says Thursday that two juveniles have been charged after several slides at a park were doused with acid this summer and four children were injured

title: CVS removing decongestant from shelves after FDA panel says it's ineffective
description: CVS Health is planning to remove one type of a common decongestant from shelves after an FDA advisory committee voted that it was ineffective.

title: Kenneth Chesebro takes last-minute plea deal in Georgia election interference case
description: Kenneth Chesebro, a key co-defendant in former President Trump's Georgia election interference case, has taken a last-minute plea deal in the case.

title: China sends an envoy to the Middle East in a sign of its ambition to play larger role
description: A top Chinese envoy says that China and Russia share the same position on the Palestinian issue and plan to try to work together to cool the situation and help establish a two-state solution for Israel and the Palestinians

title: Alex Jones ordered to pay judgment to Sandy Hook families, despite bankruptcy
description: Judge rules Alex Jones bankruptcy doesn't protect him from paying defamation judgment to Sandy Hook shooting parents.

title: UK stage and screen star Haydn Gwynne dies at 66 after cancer diagnosis
description: British stage and screen start Haydn Gwynne has died at 66 after being diagnosed with cancer

title: Cleveland museum sues to stop seizure of statue believed to depict Marcus Aurelius
description: The Cleveland Museum of Art has sued New York City authorities over their seizure of a headless bronze statue believed to depict the Roman emperor and philosopher Marcus Aurelius

title: Man convicted of murdering wife in dispute over 'Zombie House Flipping' appearance
description: A Florida man has been found guilty of murdering his wife after a dispute over whether they should appear together on a home-renovation television show

title: WATCH:  Hero bus driver saves boy from choking on coin
description: Radford Baker has been in transportation for 17 years and this was the first time she's had to save a child's life.

title: WATCH:  Israel releases footage of night attacks across Gaza
description: Israel on Friday released footage of night attacks across Gaza, saying it hit what it described as over a hundred operational targets of "terrorist organization" in the Gaza Strip.

title: WATCH:  Dolphin delights toddler by stopping for 'chat' at aquarium
description: A friendly dolphin decided to stop and "chat" with a delighted toddler at an aquarium.

title: Dutch king, queen confronted by protesters on visit to South Africa slavery museum
description: Angry protesters in Cape Town have confronted the king and queen of the Netherlands as they visited a museum that traces part of their country's 150-year involvement in slavery in South Africa

title: Reward offered after body of man missing for 9 years found in freezer of wine bar
description: Police in London are offering a “substantial reward” for information regarding the death of a man whose body was found in the basement freezer of a disused wine bar.

title: Maryland circuit court judge Andrew Wilkinson shot and killed outside home
description: The Washington County Sheriff's Office in Maryland has confirmed that Circuit Court Judge Andrew Wilkinson, 52, was fatally shot on Thursday night.

title: Baltimore firefighter dies and 4 others are injured battling rowhouse fire
description: City officials say a rapidly intensifying blaze that engulfed multiple rowhouses in northwest Baltimore left one firefighter dead and four others injured

title: Travis King, solider who crossed border into North Korea, charged with desertion
description: Army private Travis King, who crossed the border into North Korea before being returned to the U.S. in September, has been charged with desertion, according to a source.

title: Army private who fled to North Korea charged with desertion, held by US military, officials tell AP
description: An Army private who fled to North Korea before being returned home to the United States earlier this month has been detained by the U.S. military

title: A main suspect in the killing of Haitian President Jovenel Moïse has been arrested after 2 years
description: Haiti's national police say a former justice official considered one of the main suspects in the killing of Haitian President Jovenel Moïse in 2021 has been arrested

title: French officials suspect pranksters in a rash of fake bomb threats and warn of heavy punishments
description: The Palace of Versailles was forced to evacuate visitors for the fourth time in less than a week for a security check after a bomb alert
